subject: host-boot-time: Add `setDuration` and `notify` command
commitMessage:
host-boot-time: Add `setDuration` and `notify` command

These 2 commands are for the `btmanager` feature in the google-misc.
Basically `btmanager` is a daemon for monitoring the host reboot process.
This is useful for profiling the reboot process and knowing how to
optimize it.

Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54398
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54399
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54420
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54421
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54422
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54705
Reference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54501

Tested:
```
machine# cat /usr/share/btmanager/resume.json | grep "ABC"
machine# ipmitool raw 0x2e 0x32 0x79 0x2b 0x00 0x10 0x03 0x41 0x42 0x43 0xa5 0xbb 0x0d 0x00 0x00 0x00 0x00 0x00
 79 2b 00 10 01
machine# cat /usr/share/btmanager/resume.json | grep "ABC"
            "ABC": 900005,

machine# cat /usr/share/btmanager/resume.json | grep "CurrentTimePoint"
        "CurrentTimePoint": 3
machine# ipmitool raw 0x2e 0x32 0x79 0x2b 0x00 0x11 0x04
[DEBUG]: current timepoint = 3, next timepoint = 4, timestamp = 40959110
 79 2b 00 11 86 fc 70 02 00 00 00 00
machine# cat /usr/share/btmanager/final.json | grep "CurrentTimePoint"
        "CurrentTimePoint": 4
```

Signed-off-by: Michael Shen <gpgpgp@google.com>
Change-Id: I7ed3ce2045e3fa7c65860e8689d8e5b1fb0cb918

Sorry I didn't get you point.
You are asking why do we need 2 similar functions `hostBootTimeSetDuration` and `dbusSetDuration`?
Or you are asking what's the purpose of `hostBootTimeSetDuration` and `hostBootTimeNotify`?

The answer for former one is that I need to mock `dbusSetDuration` in the unit test so that I can test `hostBootTimeSetDuration`.

The answer for later one is that this CL is supporting `btmanager`.
btmanager is a new added service for monitor the host boot process. The code is in the review process on openbmc/google-misc. https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/google-misc/+/54501/4
yeah, I just meant that we need more detail on what the service does. Can you link the change to the commit message?
